The South African Policing Union (Sapu) feels disappointed and embarrassed about the parade at the funeral of Richard Maponya. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -The South African Policing Union (Sapu) feels disappointed and embarrassed about the parade at the funeral of Richard Maponya. The unco-ordinated salutes drew ridicule on social media. “We have also called for the judicial commission of inquiry so that it be the one that advises the president on ills that are inhabiting policing to do its professional work.” Maponya was laid to rest on Tuesday.